  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Rinse the <strong>red lentils</strong> in a sieve under cold running water</p><p>Add the <strong>rinsed lentils</strong> to a heatproof bowl, cover them <strong>boiled water </strong>(just enough to cover them) and set aside for 15-20 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-red-lentil-pancakes-with-beetroot-chutney/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the lentils are softening, drain the<strong> beetroot </strong>in a sieve over the sink then grate and squeeze out any excess water</p><p>Peel and slice the<strong> shallot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> finely</p><p>Chop the <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Strip the <strong>mint </strong>leaves from their stems and chop them roughly, discard the stems</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-red-lentil-pancakes-with-beetroot-chutney/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>grated beetroot </strong>to a medium sized pot with the <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!),<strong> tamarind paste</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water</strong></p><p>Season with<strong> </strong>a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and 2 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>and bring to a boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to low and cook for 10-15 min, stirring frequently, or until thickened to a jam-like consistency – this is your <strong>beetroot chutney</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-red-lentil-pancakes-with-beetroot-chutney/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the chutney is cooking, drain and rinse the <strong>chickpeas</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>drained chickpeas</strong> to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong>, <strong>half</strong> the <strong>curry powder</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for 10-15 min or until crisp – these are your <strong>crispy curried chickpeas</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-red-lentil-pancakes-with-beetroot-chutney/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>carrot</strong> <strong>&</strong> <strong>cabbage slaw mix</strong> to a large bowl with the <strong>sliced shallot</strong>, <strong>cider vinegar</strong>, <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong> and <strong>chopped mint</strong></p><p>Season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and 1/2 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and mix it all together – this is your <strong>ginger</strong> <strong>slaw</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-red-lentil-pancakes-with-beetroot-chutney/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once softened, drain the <strong>soaked lentils</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>drained lentils </strong>to a <strong>food processor</strong> with 150ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong>, 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and the <strong>remaining curry powder</strong> and blitz until smooth</p><p>Once smooth, transfer the <strong>lentil mixture</strong> to a bowl with <strong>half</strong> the<strong> chopped coriander</strong> and <strong>nigella seeds </strong>and mix until fully combined – this is your <strong>batter</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-red-lentil-pancakes-with-beetroot-chutney/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, pour exactly 1/2<strong> </strong><span class=\"text-danger\">[1/4]</span> of the <strong>batter</strong> into the pan and tilt it in a circular motion so that the mixture spreads evenly over the base and cook for 3-4 min on each side<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>or until set</p><p>Transfer to a plate and cover with <strong>tin foil </strong>then repeat for the final 1 <span class=\"text-danger\">[3] </span>pancake<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> – these are your <strong>red lentil pancakes</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-red-lentil-pancakes-with-beetroot-chutney/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>red lentil pancakes </strong>topped with the <strong>beetroot chutney</strong>,<strong> ginger slaw </strong>and <strong>crispy curried chickpeas</strong></p><p>Drizzle the <strong>cultured coconut </strong>and garnish with the <strong>remaining coriander</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
